        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 4:28PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 428 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Balko, or 12 miles southwest of Beaver, moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Balko.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
